      SEARCH: Wednesday, October 08, 2008 News Sports Opinion Lifestyle Multimedia Blogs Info Local Ads Local | | | One killed in Fabyan Parkway crash ( No comments posted. ) BATAVIA -- One person was killed this morning in a crash on Fabyan Parkway between Main Street and Hughes Road in unincorporated Kane County near Batavia. Kane County Sheriff's police are investigating the crash, which happened around 5:30 a.m. Police said they arrived on the scene to find two cars were involved in the crash. One person was taken to Delnor Hospital in Geneva with injuries that did not appear life threatening. And one person was pronounced dead at the scene, police said. Fabyan Parkway is closed between Main Street and Hughes Road as police investigate the crash, and police said they did not know when the road would reopen. The following are comments from the readers. In no way do they represent the view of KCChronicle.com or Shaw Newspapers. You must register with a valid email to post comments. Only your member ID will be posted with the comments. Registered users sign in here: Become a Registered User *Member ID: *Password: Remember login? ( We detected you need to update your Flash Player to version 8 or greater . You can and install the latest Flash Player from . Â©2008 Kane County Chronicle. All rights reserved. Published in Geneva, Illinois, USA by Shaw Suburban Media, a Division of | | | | | | | 